MATCH_TOOL: Bash
MATCH_PATTERN: (^|&&|;|\|\|)\s*npm run dev(\s|$)
ADVISORY: |
  `npm run dev` runs turborepo from the current working directory, which
  selects tasks based on that directory's package.json:

  - From repo root / worktree root: starts ALL dev tasks (lobby :3000,
    client :5173, game-server :8787) — usually what you want.
  - From `apps/game-server`: starts ONLY wrangler dev (8787-8788). No
    client vite, no lobby.
  - From `apps/client`: starts ONLY vite (5173).
  - From `apps/lobby`: starts ONLY next dev (3000).

  Real session cost: typechecked from `apps/game-server`, then ran
  `npm run dev` without cd, silently started wrangler instead of vite.
  Had to kill it and restart from `apps/client`.

  If you want a specific app, be explicit:
      cd apps/client && npm run dev -- --port 5175

  If you want everything, cd to the repo/worktree root first.

  This is distinct from the "wrong worktree" trap (see
  finite-dev-server-wrong-worktree). This one is "wrong app WITHIN the
  correct worktree."
